&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Company Name: &lt;/strong&gt;Hellbender Inc.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Title: &lt;/strong&gt;Perception Engineer&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Department: &lt;/strong&gt;Engineering&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Report to: &lt;/strong&gt;VP of Software Engineering&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who We Are:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hellbender Inc. is a Pennsylvania Benefit Corporation who partners with innovators to mature their Artificial Intelligence enabled computing sensors and produce their solutions onshore at prototype to high volumes.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hellbender is intentionally forming an inclusive work environment and is committed to uplifting the historically marginalized identities including veterans, women, trans and non-white races in our community and industry.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Summary:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Perception Engineer at Hellbender you will help lead the design and development of AI-enabled computer vision solutions for a wide variety of industrial and commercial applications. For this role you will need to possess a strong background in building advanced perception models, state estimation, object tracking, and sensor fusion for use in autonomous systems. United States veteran and diverse candidates are encouraged to apply at any experience level.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Duties and Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and optimize computer vision and machine learning algorithms for object detection, classification, tracking, and scene understanding in varied and dynamic environments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Utilize data from a variety of sensors, including cameras, LiDAR, and radar, to create comprehensive perception systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implementation and evaluation of calibration procedures, particularly with stereo and sensor fusion scenarios&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct extensive testing and validation of perception systems; document and troubleshoot issues as they arise&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with hardware engineers to calibrate sensors and integrate perception capabilities into broader autonomous systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with other software engineers to deploy perception models in both prototyping and production environments&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the team during the proposal phase, by aiding the specification and selection of appropriate sensors and compute needs for each application.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications, Skills, and Attributes:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Must haves:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s or Master&#39;s degree in Computer Science, Robotics, Electrical Engineering, or a related field, with a focus on computer vision or machine learning&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficient in programming languages and tools commonly used in perception systems development (Python, C++, OpenCV, etc.)&amp;nbsp; and experience with relevant AI and machine learning frameworks (TensorFlow, PyTorch, etc.)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+ years of professional experience building perception systems that incorporate camera, LiDAR, and radar data&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nice to have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience designing and developing computer vision, machine learning, and sensor fusion for autonomous systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with procedural 3D modeling and photorealistic rendering&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience deploying machine learning models on embedded platforms, such as NVIDIA Jetson or Hailo TPUs, is&lt;em&gt; highly preferred&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Type:&lt;/strong&gt; Full-time&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits:&amp;nbsp;&

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Company Name: &lt;/strong&gt;Hellbender Inc.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Title&lt;/strong&gt;: SMT Operator&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Department&lt;/strong&gt;: Production&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Report to: &lt;/strong&gt;Production Manager&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hellbender Inc. is a Pennsylvania Benefit Corporation who partners with innovators to mature their Artificial Intelligence enabled computing sensors and produce their solutions onshore at prototype to high volumes.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hellbender is intentionally forming an inclusive work environment and is committed to uplifting the historically marginalized identities including veterans, women, trans and non-white races in our community and industry.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Summary:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The SMT Operator will assist in the manufacturing of printed circuit boards, product assemblies, and report to the operations manager. This person will work with a small team to perform assembly of electronic components that includes preparation, placement and installation using a modern SMT line. Our line includes a Speedprint 710 stencil printer, Europlacer iiNEO+ pick and place machine, BTU reflow oven, and Omron 730 AOI machine. We perform a high mix run of low to medium sized production batches.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential Duties and Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Programming and maintenance of the SMT assembly line and any related equipment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform all facets of surface mount assembly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Primary responsibility for line operation including screen printer, pick and place machine, and reflow oven, Automatic Optical Inspection machine, and ancillary SMT line equipment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Operate the equipment, including understanding the sequence of events, the control panel, and indicators, and understanding how to replenish supplies and components per Standard Operating Procedures&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Set-up of the equipment, and maintain operation, which includes machine adjustments and ability to perform set-up (feeder loading and changing) per the manufacturing instructions and Standard Operating Procedures&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ownership of general equipment cleaning and upkeep per the Standard Operating Procedures&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manual assembly of electronic components including some complex part installations, custom specs and quality standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform hand soldering, inspection, and rework, SMT, mixed assemblies and custom parts as per Engineering specifications and IPC workmanship standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Component preparation, placement, and installation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be able to work on various aspects of the manufacturing operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in training and certification programs to ensure job knowledge and skills set.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications, Skill, and Attributes&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge in printed circuit board related processes – soldering, cleaning, and repairing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Specialized SMT knowledge is ideal&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands on manufacturing skills such as manual soldering&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to read and to work from schematics, process sheets, a sample or other work instructions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be able to work independently with minimal supervision&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comply with all department and company rules&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working with extremely small parts using a microscope and small hand tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong attention to detail and focus on quality&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Technical communication skills – must be able to interface with engineering and purchasing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use hand, air, and power tools&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Company Name:&lt;/strong&gt; Hellbender Inc.&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Title: &lt;/strong&gt;Technical Project Manager&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Department:&lt;/strong&gt; Operations&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Report to:&lt;/strong&gt; VP of Operations&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
