&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish trust and build effective relationships with customers, executives, engineering&amp;nbsp;and production teams, and a variety of cross-functional stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage and ensure successful, on-time, on-budget delivery of engineering solutions for&amp;nbsp;multiple concurrent projects&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Organize project teams by assigning responsibilities, developing schedules, and&amp;nbsp;determining resource requirements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify risks to the contracted scope and develop mitigation plans&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interface with all departments including design, procurement, manufacturing, assembly,&amp;nbsp;and testing to ensure project alignment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support business development and new work proposals, and generate additional scopes&amp;nbsp;of work for current projects as required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications, Skills, and Attributes:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A Bachelor&#39;s Degree in Computer Science, Materials Science, Robotics, or equivalent&amp;nbsp;education&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience leading technology based products through the various developmental&amp;nbsp;phases including requirements definition, design, testing, field trials, and production&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience balancing resources across multiple projects, as well as tracking scope,&amp;nbsp;schedule, and budget&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong experience with Microsoft Office Suite, software configuration tools, and project&amp;nbsp;management systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience leading cross-functional teams of varying skills and experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent written and oral communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with software, firmware, mechanical, and/ or electrical engineering&amp;nbsp;teams as a developer preferred&lt;/li&gt;
